This paper is about recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also deals with temporal dynamics, which is a topic of interest in the social and information networks (cs.SOC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new graph-based approach for modeling user-item interactions, which could be relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on real-world datasets, which suggests that the systems and information (cs.SI) sub-category could also be relevant.
